sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant C as Client
    participant A as API Server
    participant D as Database
    participant E as Email Service

    Note over U,E: Registration Flow (FEAT-001)

    U->>C: Fill registration form
    C->>A: POST /auth/register
    A->>D: Check email exists
    alt Email exists
        A-->>C: 409 Email already exists
        C-->>U: Show error
    else Email available
        A->>A: Hash password (bcrypt)
        A->>D: Create user (unverified)
        A->>A: Generate verification token
        A->>D: Store token
        A->>E: Send verification email
        E-->>U: Email with verify link
        A-->>C: 201 Registration successful
        C-->>U: "Check your email"
    end

    Note over U,E: Email Verification

    U->>C: Click verify link
    C->>A: POST /auth/verify-email {token}
    A->>D: Validate token
    alt Token valid
        A->>D: Mark email verified
        A->>D: Invalidate token
        A-->>C: 200 Email verified
        C-->>U: "Email verified, you can login"
    else Token invalid/expired
        A-->>C: 400 Invalid token
        C-->>U: Show error with resend option
    end

    Note over U,E: Login Flow (FEAT-002)

    U->>C: Enter credentials
    C->>A: POST /auth/login {email, password}
    A->>D: Find user by email
    alt User not found
        A-->>C: 401 Invalid credentials
    else User found
        A->>A: Verify password
        alt Password incorrect
            A->>D: Record failed attempt
            alt Attempts >= 5
                A->>D: Lock account (15 min)
            end
            A-->>C: 401 Invalid credentials
        else Password correct
            alt Email not verified
                A-->>C: 403 Email not verified
            else Account locked
                A-->>C: 423 Account locked
            else All checks pass
                A->>A: Generate JWT + refresh token
                A->>D: Store session
                A-->>C: 200 {access_token, refresh_token}
                C->>C: Store tokens securely
                C-->>U: Redirect to dashboard
            end
        end
    end

    Note over U,E: Token Refresh

    C->>A: POST /auth/refresh {refresh_token}
    A->>D: Validate refresh token
    alt Valid
        A->>A: Generate new access token
        A-->>C: 200 {access_token}
    else Invalid/expired
        A-->>C: 401 Invalid token
        C->>C: Clear tokens
        C-->>U: Redirect to login
    end
